&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking to recruit highly motivated Registered Nursing Associates. You will be working with our existing registered nurses and nursing care support workers in a variety of areas and services in this new role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated, enthusiastic and resilient individuals to help us continue to develop this new and exciting role in the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have excellent clinical, written and verbal communication skills and have completed the Trainee Nursing Associates course, gaining NMC registration&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will offer you a two year preceptorship and further development opportunities which as well as offering you the opportunity to consolidate your role could provide you with a structured career pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we offer a great team environment, learning and development opportunities and supervision support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to work in a hospital that values you, supports you in allowing you the time to really care and is committed to your professional development then apply today!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Arran Rogers - Arran.Rogers@royalberkshire.nhs.uk, 0118 322 7193&lt;/p&gt;
